title: Handy Manny
description:
My daughters really like this show, so I'm sure there are some other kids out there that like it as well. I love this show because it teaches kids how to get along with one another in a group and solve problems within that group in an easy to understand way.

Manny is a repairman with a toolbox full of talking tools, all of which are cleverly named: for example, the measuring tape is Stretch, the hammer is Pat. Together Manny and his tools take on a variety of jobs, which always require thinking through possible ways of getting them done.
Manny is a Latino, and speaks a mixture of English and Spanish, as do some of the other characters on the show; only one of his tools has a Latino accent -- Felipe, the phillips screwdriver. When other characters greet them, they typically say, "Hola, Manny. Hello, Tools."


Included are:

1) amigo grande
2) not so fast food
3) rusty to the rescue
4) The handy mandy music video.( not a episode, but a cute little video)
